e some of the proposed transfers of Syrian army officers have been carried out, the army chief of staff, as a result of a compromise among army factions, is reported to have agreed to retain leftist Lieutenant Colonel Sarraj as G-2, for the present.\n\nThe Egyptian embassy apparently is supporting the Sarraj-leftist group.\n\nThe situation remains unsettled. Leftist moves to involve \"street\" support are suggested by reports that Damascus youth were issued Czech submachine guns on 20 March in preparation for a \"parade\" on 24 or 25 March. Several thousand members of the leftist paramilitary \"Futuwa\" organization are believed similarly armed", "token_count": 108, "token_end_0based": 107, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "1 the situation in syria comment on while some of the proposed transfers of syrian army officers have been carried out the army chief of staff as a result of a compromise among army factions is reported to have agreed to retain leftist lieutenant colonel sarraj as g-2 for the present the egyptian embassy apparently is supporting the sarraj-leftist group the situation remains unsettled leftist moves to involve street support are suggested by reports that damascus youth were issued czech submachine guns on 20 march in preparation for a parade on 24 or 25 march several thousand members of the leftist paramilitary futuwa organization are believed similarly armed", "unred_source_page": 4}
